Sentencas: Interfacial cracking resistance of a joint between a glass ceramic sealant (GC-9) and interconnect stainless steel (Crofer 22 H) for planar solid oxide fuel cells is investigated.
Titulo: Interfacial fracture resistance of the joint of a solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic sealant with metallic interconnect

Sentencas: Interfacial fracture energy is measured at room temperature to 800 degrees C using a four-point bending test technique.
Titulo: Interfacial fracture resistance of the joint of a solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic sealant with metallic interconnect

Sentencas: A heat treatment of 100 h or 1000 h at 800 degrees C is applied for studying the thermal aging effect.
Titulo: Interfacial fracture resistance of the joint of a solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic sealant with metallic interconnect

Sentencas: Results show the variation trend of interfacial fracture energy with temperature is similar for all given material conditions.
Titulo: Interfacial fracture resistance of the joint of a solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic sealant with metallic interconnect

Sentencas: Interfacial fracture energy increases with temperature to reach a peak value at 700 degrees C and then drops at temperature above 700 degrees
Titulo: Interfacial fracture resistance of the joint of a solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic sealant with metallic interconnect

Sentencas: C. A 100-h aging treatment does not change the interfacial fracture energy significantly, compared to the non-aged condition.
Titulo: Interfacial fracture resistance of the joint of a solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic sealant with metallic interconnect

Sentencas: The 1000 h-aged joint, however, has greater interfacial fracture energy than the non-aged and 100 h-aged joints at 700 degrees C-800 degrees C. Two types of cracking path in the interior of fracture surface are identified.
Titulo: Interfacial fracture resistance of the joint of a solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic sealant with metallic interconnect

Sentencas: Firstly, delamination takes place at the interface between the glass-ceramic substrate and chromate layer.
Titulo: Interfacial fracture resistance of the joint of a solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic sealant with metallic interconnect

Sentencas: Secondly, cracking occurs within the chromate layer.
Titulo: Interfacial fracture resistance of the joint of a solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic sealant with metallic interconnect

Sentencas: However, for the 1000 h-aged joints tested at 700 degrees C-800 degrees C, fracture at the highly oxidized, peripheral regions takes place within the glass-ceramic layer.
Titulo: Interfacial fracture resistance of the joint of a solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic sealant with metallic interconnect
